fields.Title: YARD / TRASH
fields.Description: You can click on the trash container. This lets you see the padlock has a Whirling-in-Rags logo on it -> go to Garte -> ask for key -> open container - > get your paperwork

fields.Title: Trash Container: "This trash container is locked. The..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This trash container is locked. The sliding lid has a padlock that says "Whirling-in-Rags."

fields.Title: Trash Container: "The dumpster is goading you. It thi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The dumpster is goading you. It thinks you're weak.

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Figures.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Figures."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""The belt is missing. That's it. Do..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The belt is missing. That's it. Do you see anything else in there? I have another bag here..."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Cuno can hear you, cop -- and Cuno..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Cuno can hear you, cop -- and Cuno don't know shit about the rags, okay? You don't have to come asking about them again like some bitch."

fields.Title: Jump to: [Tutorial Agent: "Some items, such as the ledger you..."]
You: ""I speaketh the tongue.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I speaketh the tongue."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Do-eth thou also thorough inventor..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Do-eth thou also thorough inventories?" He points to the ruined notes. "You should take stock of your notes, make sure it's all there. Official notes contain informants' names. If some of it has fallen into the hands of the RCM's adversaries, bloodletting may well ensue."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I see, yes. You're what we call a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I see, yes. You're what we call a *bad ass*, aren't you?" He makes little quotation marks around the words, indicating he is unsure of its actual badassery.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "With effort, he looks at you."
fields.Dialogue Text: With effort, he looks at you.

fields.Title: Trash Container: "*Just* a trash container? There is..."
fields.Dialogue Text: *Just* a trash container? There is no such thing.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""None. Because they don't exist.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "None. Because they don't exist."

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Did someone say *prybar*?!"
fields.Dialogue Text: Did someone say *prybar*?!

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Prybar, prybar, your palms yearn it..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Prybar, prybar, your palms yearn it's cold touch. To grasp it once more, as you've done so many times...

fields.Title: Trash Container: "This is where you belong..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is where you belong...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "Soggy cartons and rags look back at..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Soggy cartons and rags look back at him. "Oh yes -- and it would also be appropriate to start taking notes on the case. It's what cops do."

fields.Title: You: "I'm not going to do anything."
fields.Dialogue Text: I'm not going to do anything.

fields.Title: Logic: "Exactly. Open your official investi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Exactly. Open your official investigation.

fields.Title: Jump to: [Trash Container: "You pick out a broken mug, with an..."]
Trash Container: "Unsatisfying. Hurtful. You hear a r..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Unsatisfying. Hurtful. You hear a ringing sound, but not quite hollow. The can seems to be full...

fields.Title: You: "Say nothing."
fields.Dialogue Text: Say nothing.

fields.Title: Trash Container: "With a well-oiled crack the lock po..."
fields.Dialogue Text: With a well-oiled crack the lock pops open. It should now be possible to simply raise the lid...

fields.Title: Trash Container: "And is that a Cordon Electrics pre..."
fields.Dialogue Text: And is that a Cordon Electrics pre amp with Elektra f2 tubes? It is! That catches quite a price, we're talking 12,000 easy. Unless you're into hi-fi yourself?

fields.Title: Trash Container: "A blue piece of plastic sticks out..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A blue piece of plastic sticks out from the apple peels. It's *shiny*. Looks like the corner of something...

fields.Title: Cunoesse: ""The fuck's he on about -- *kid*?!"..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The fuck's he on about -- *kid*?!" the one behind the fence yells. "You hear that, Cuno? He thinks you're an infant or some shit."

fields.Title: Trash Container: "Soggy carton and some kind of food..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Soggy carton and some kind of food sludge welcome you back, uninvitingly. Smells like the wrong choice.

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Wow, went off script there, getting..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Wow, went off script there, getting your ass handed to you. You shouldn't go picking fights if your rhetorical faculties haven't suggested it.

fields.Title: You: ""Yes, I *feel* like there's somethi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, I *feel* like there's something in there."

fields.Title: You: "Fuck yeah! Prybar!"
fields.Dialogue Text: Fuck yeah! Prybar!

fields.Title: You: "What's a prybar?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What's a prybar?

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "*Still* not force time. You're just..."
fields.Dialogue Text: *Still* not force time. You're just not getting there... the prybar is primed, but you lack the ability.

fields.Title: You: "What am I supposed to do?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What am I supposed to do?

fields.Title: Variable["yard.trash_kim_turned_from_digging"] == true  and  Variable["yard.trash_interfacing_deluxe_content"]  == false  and  Variable["yard.trash_mug"] == false
Variable["yard.trash_kim_turned_from_digging"] == true  and  Variable["yard.trash_interfacing_deluxe_content"]  == false  and  Variable["yard.trash_mug"] == false

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["yard.trash_kim_turned_from_digging"] == true  and  Variable["yard.trash_interfacing_deluxe_content"]  == false  and  Variable["yard.trash_mug"] == false

fields.Title: !(Variable["yard.trash_kim_turned_from_digging"] == true  and  Variable["yard.trash_interfacing_deluxe_content"]  == false  and  Variable["yard.trash_mug"] == false)

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: (Variable["yard.trash_kim_turned_from_digging"] == true  and  Variable["yard.trash_interfacing_deluxe_content"]  == false  and  Variable["yard.trash_mug"] == false) == false

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""The strange thing is -- we don't h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The strange thing is -- we don't have to." He smiles. "We have the *key* remember. The manager gave you the key."

fields.Title: Trash Container: "The smell of rotten food rises to g..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The smell of rotten food rises to greet you. You see soggy cartons, dirty rags, and organic waste.
fields.Sequence: HideActualHeld(); PlayAnimation(Tequila Sunset, lid_open); PlayAnimation(bin_lid, lid_open);

fields.Title: You: ""The kid said he didn't know anythi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The kid said he didn't know anything about the clothes."

fields.Title: Trash Container: "The garbage stinks in front of you,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The garbage stinks in front of you, overflowing with soggy cartons, dirty rags, and organic waste.

fields.Title: You: "No! Not like this! (Crawl out of th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No! Not like this! (Crawl out of the trash.)

fields.Title: Logic: "Oh, yes you are. It's *fundamental*..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Oh, yes you are. It's *fundamental* to proper police procedure to start keeping notes on the case at hand. Open your official investigation.

fields.Title: You: ""Then we should open it immediately!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Then we should open it immediately!"

fields.Title: Logic: "He might also have information -- t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He might also have information -- this is better than the prybar idea.

fields.Title: Empathy: "He's enjoying your little failure...."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's enjoying your little failure. He finds it amusing, he's revelling in the sweaty rage on your face.

fields.Title: Cuno: ""No you weren't. If you were you'd..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No you weren't. If you were you'd stick that shitto..." He makes a move with his hands. "In that staple or some shit. That little ring that has the lock in it. Then twist that shit, it's the weak spot."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""We're just in time." The lieutenan..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We're just in time." The lieutenant peers in. "This hasn't been emptied for over a week."

fields.Title: You: "An antique?"
fields.Dialogue Text: An antique?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Alright. We should go to Garte aga..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Alright. We should go to Garte again and ask if he knows who put the clothes in the trash. It could be as simple as someone from the hostel cleaning the yard, or *that* one..." He nods toward the red-haired boy behind him. "I'd advise *against* confronting that force."

fields.Title: Jump to: [Trash Container: "The smell of rotten food rises to g..."]
Trash Container: "The smell of rotten food rises up a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The smell of rotten food rises up at you as you climb inside the trash container.

fields.Title: You: ""I'm so disappointed right now. I t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm so disappointed right now. I thought there was a Remote Viewers Division."

fields.Title: You: ""Oh. Okay.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh. Okay."

fields.Title: You: ""Seems like a reasonable assumption.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Seems like a reasonable assumption."

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "There's something in there. Not nec..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There's something in there. Not necessarily connected to the case -- but still...

fields.Title: You: ""But I wanted to use the prybar......"
fields.Dialogue Text: "But I wanted to use the prybar... I feel like I'm losing out on something not using the prybar."

fields.Title: You: ""Fuck you, Cuno.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Fuck you, Cuno."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant nods, then looks bac..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant nods, then looks back into the trash container.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I don't know either..." He points..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't know either..." He points to the ruined notes. "You should take stock of your notes, make sure it's all there. Official notes contain informants' names. If some have fallen into the hands of the RCM's adversaries, bloodletting may well ensue."

fields.Title: Cunoesse: ""The fuck's he on about -- *kids*?!..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The fuck's he on about -- *kids*?!" The one behind the fence yells. "You hear that, Cuno? He thinks you're an infant or something."

fields.Title: Trash Container: "...what's *this*?"
fields.Dialogue Text: ...what's *this*?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""What do you mean *feel*?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What do you mean *feel*?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""All the detectives from all the Pr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "All the detectives from all the Precincts who experience extrasensory perception go to the Remote Viewers Division. Their work is invaluable to the force."

fields.Title: You: ""How do we get the lock open?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "How do we get the lock open?"

fields.Title: You: "Dive further..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Dive further...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Officer," the lieutenant adds, "Th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Officer," the lieutenant adds, "This is sensitive information. You need to take this seriously."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""We could try using a prybar -- the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We could try using a prybar -- the one you took from my motor carriage. Or..."

fields.Title: You: "Pick at the rags."
fields.Dialogue Text: Pick at the rags.

fields.Title: Trash Container: "The trash container stands in the s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The trash container stands in the spring snow.

fields.Title: You: ""Damn, this reminds me: I got side-..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Damn, this reminds me: I got side- tracked asking Cuno about the rags... The damned FALN pants got in the way. We should ask again, Kim."

fields.Title: You: "Grab them."
fields.Dialogue Text: Grab them.

fields.Title: Trash Container: "As the legs of the slime-covered je..."
fields.Dialogue Text: As the legs of the slime-covered jeans begin to unspool from the garbage, a rank corpse smell fills the air.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "His gaze is focused on something ne..."
fields.Dialogue Text: His gaze is focused on something nebulous in the far distance. On nothing in particular.

fields.Title: You: ""See you in the morning.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "See you in the morning."

fields.Title: You: "Time for bed again. Crawl inside fo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Time for bed again. Crawl inside for real...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""No, because they don't exist.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, because they don't exist."

fields.Title: You: "Why am I looking at you, trash cont..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Why am I looking at you, trash container? You're just a trash container.

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "You stick the prybar into the fissu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You stick the prybar into the fissure beneath the lid and push down. It doesn't take much force -- with a satisfying *crack,* the metal gives way. You can open the lid now.

fields.Title: You: "Close the lid."
fields.Dialogue Text: Close the lid.

fields.Title: You: "What's a nock cannon?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What's a nock cannon?

fields.Title: You: "Where?! I can't see it."
fields.Dialogue Text: Where?! I can't see it.

fields.Title: You: "(Take the mug.)"
fields.Dialogue Text: (Take the mug.)

fields.Title: Trash Container: "Among the threadbare kitchen towels..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Among the threadbare kitchen towels, something catches your eye -- a pair of denim trousers?

fields.Title: You: "Bag the shirt."
fields.Dialogue Text: Bag the shirt.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "The rest of the rags are just kitch..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The rest of the rags are just kitchen-variety waste. A yellow old mug that catches your eye. But other than that...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Officer, is that your... paperwork?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Officer, is that your... paperwork?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It is, look..." He points to the c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It is, look..." He points to the clipboard. "The plastic has the RCM street grid on it. You've even got an autopsy form in there..." A miserable looking slip of paper sticks to the board.

fields.Title: Interfacing: "It does? Maybe it does. It *might*..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It does? Maybe it does. It *might* have been thrown out by your hand. Feels like that anyway -- like *stuffed* it somewhere. Not in this trash though. How it got here you haven't a clue.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""If you don't mind me asking -- how..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "If you don't mind me asking -- how did this get in the trash?"
fields.Alternate1: "If you don't mind my asking, how could you have let your paperwork end up in the trash?"

fields.Title: You: ""I don't know.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't know."

fields.Title: Authority: "Be untroubled. If anything, this sm..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Be untroubled. If anything, this small moment has made him respect you more.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Drop them in here, officer." The l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Drop them in here, officer." The lieutenant produces a black plastic bag marked *evidence* from his pocket.

fields.Title: You: ""It's just a hunch. Maybe someone t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's just a hunch. Maybe someone threw something in there?"

fields.Title: You: ""What kind of extra-natural abiliti..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What kind of extra-natural abilities do they possess?"

fields.Title: You: ""No *or*. Prybar!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No *or*. Prybar!"

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Ask *the manager*? Bullshit! Go str..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Ask *the manager*? Bullshit! Go straight for the prybar and pry this baby wide open!

fields.Title: Trash Container: "The lock says Whirling-in-Rags. May..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lock says Whirling-in-Rags. Maybe the proprietor has the key? Who knows what secrets wait inside...

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Force time isn't happening. You've..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Force time isn't happening. You've jammed the prybar under the lid but it just isn't bending.

fields.Title: Cunoesse: ""What are you his fuckin' sidekick..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What are you his fuckin' sidekick now, Cun'? Don't listen to him pig, you were good."

fields.Title: You: "Open the lid."
fields.Dialogue Text: Open the lid.

fields.Title: You: ""I don't know *what* this is.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't know *what* this is."

fields.Title: You: ""By *early stages* you mean these w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "By *early stages* you mean these were taken from him no more than two days after his death?"

fields.Title: You: "What I should do is get back to tha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What I should do is get back to that garbage. (Decline.)

fields.Title: Trash Container: "Good choice. Soggy carton and some..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Good choice. Soggy carton and some kind of food sludge welcome you back, invitingly.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Understood." He nods, reverting hi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Understood." He nods, reverting his attention to the container, still stinking in front of you.

fields.Title: You: ""Sorry it had to be this way.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sorry it had to be this way."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "He nods. Absent-mindedly, he reache..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He nods. Absent-mindedly, he reaches for a cigarette; no sooner has it left his pocket than he catches himself.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant greets you with a sm..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant greets you with a small nod, as if you'd just taken a momentary pause to tie a shoelace.

fields.Title: You: "I should get you open, trash contai..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I should get you open, trash container.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""There isn't -- but we should still..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There isn't -- but we should still access this container."

fields.Title: Trash Container: "The body is downwind from here. May..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The body is downwind from here. Maybe you prefer the smell of garbage to the smell of death?

fields.Title: Jump to: [Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant leans in to inspect..."]
You: "The mug, I'm getting that mug too."
fields.Dialogue Text: The mug, I'm getting that mug too.

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["yard.trash_perc_knows_that_is_it"]  and  Variable["yard.trash_interfacing_deluxe_content"] == false  and  CheckItem("yellow_man_mug") == false  and  Variable["yard.trash_found_mug"] == false

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: Trash Container: "No you won't, because none of those..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No you won't, because none of those things are real. They're not actually in there. All you see is food waste and crisp wrappings.

fields.Title: Jump to: [Trash Container: "The garbage stinks in front of you,..."]
Trash Container: "Never mind, look at that fat string..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Never mind, look at that fat string of Archipelagoan pearls snaking amidst the banana peels!

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "This feels like something you shoul..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This feels like something you should return to with Lieutenant Kitsuragi present. Also, it makes you feel like an idiot for not having an evidence bag on you -- what will you do with a dead man's trousers?

fields.Title: You: "What?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It would also not hurt to start ta..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It would also not hurt to start taking notes on the case. Anyway, where were we..." The lieutenant peers into the trash container where soggy cartons and rags stink uninvitingly.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant averts his eyes as y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant averts his eyes as you crawl into the trash container.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "Darkness engulfs you. The stink of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Darkness engulfs you. The stink of rot nearly knocks you out. For a minute you can smell cigarette smoke wafting in from outside -- then it is gone, and you hear footsteps walking away.
fields.Sequence: PlayAnimation(Tequila Sunset, lid_sleep); PlayAnimation(bin_lid, lid_sleep); FocusCamera(Bin_Cam)@1; PlayAnimation(Kim Kitsuragi, StartSmoking)@5; PlayAnimation(Kim Cigarette, StartSmoking)@5; SemiBlack(true,2)@9;

fields.Title: You: ""Nothing.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nothing."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Interesting." The lieutenant looks..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Interesting." The lieutenant looks at the mug. "Reminds me of the mug collection we saw in our weasel's apartment. Maybe he or she has been dumping their garbage here?"

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "Yes! The one in the apartment you b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes! The one in the apartment you broke into. Interesting little clue. Surely this will yield something -- down the road...

fields.Title: You: "Kick the container."
fields.Dialogue Text: Kick the container.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""The quality of metal is not the pr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The quality of metal is not the problem. From what I see, it's sturdy enough."

fields.Title: You: "Give up."
fields.Dialogue Text: Give up.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""That's one thing off the list..."..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's one thing off the list..." The lieutenant sounds relieved. "I think we got it all."

fields.Title: Interfacing: "Yeah! Crack it open Hobocop -- this..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yeah! Crack it open Hobocop -- this is your time to shine. Dive into that dumpster for extra content!

fields.Title: You: "A cruel jest... there must be *some..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A cruel jest... there must be *something*...

fields.Title: You: "I knew it. (Withdraw from the dumps..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I knew it. (Withdraw from the dumpster's cavernous depths.)

fields.Title: You: "Pick it out."
fields.Dialogue Text: Pick it out.

fields.Title: You: ""No. It can't be.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No. It can't be."

fields.Title: Interfacing: "You don't know. It *might* have bee..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You don't know. It *might* have been by your hand, though. Feels like that. Feels like you might have stuffed it somewhere. Not in this trash though. How it got here you don't know.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Lucky we found it. You should take..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Lucky we found it. You should take stock of what remains, just to be sure some has not made it into the hands of the RCM's adversaries. Organized crime and the like. There might have been police secrets in your notes."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Yes." He nods. "I think the clothe..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes." He nods. "I think the clothes were taken off to get to that armour he wore, then discarded. They must have stripped him of it fast, too, the scavengers -- in a matter of days."

fields.Title: You: ""I don't know, man. Sounds like an..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't know, man. Sounds like an order. I don't take those."

fields.Title: Trash Container: "There's nothing more of interest in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There's nothing more of interest in this sludge of peels and meat by-product. Try the carton or those stinking rags.

fields.Title: Trash Container: "This is where you belong..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is where you belong...
fields.Sequence: PlayAnimation(Tequila Sunset, lid_sleep)->Message(sleeping); PlayAnimation(bin_lid, lid_sleep); SemiBlack(true)@Message(sleeping); PostFX(blackout-world, true)@Message(sleeping); BanishHUD(true)@Message(sleeping);FinishDialogue()@Message(sleeping);

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Beware. They're very *painful* secr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Beware. They're very *painful* secrets.

fields.Title: You: "Keep the hunch to yourself."
fields.Dialogue Text: Keep the hunch to yourself.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant leans in to inspect..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant leans in to inspect the lock.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Officer..." the lieutenant says. "..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Officer..." the lieutenant says. "Now that you have your ledger back, it would not hurt to start taking notes on the case. Officially."
fields.Alternate1: "You said you didn't want to talk about the ledger, however... now that you have it back, it would not hurt to start taking notes on the case. Officially."

fields.Title: Logic: "You have to start taking proper not..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You have to start taking proper notes on the case. Open your official investigation.

fields.Title: You: "Used to what -- dumpster diving?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Used to what -- dumpster diving?

fields.Title: You: "What's this?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What's this?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Or it may just be a coincidence. E..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Or it may just be a coincidence. Either way, something to keep in mind. What else do you see?"

fields.Title: Trash Container: "Wow, an Armistice calibre 50 nock c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Wow, an Armistice calibre 50 nock cannon, half wrapped in paper tissues! So shiny...

fields.Title: Trash Container: "It's a giant rifle and it's very ex..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's a giant rifle and it's very expensive. Not as expensive as that fat string of pearls snaking among the rotten banana peels however...

fields.Title: You: "I'll sell it."
fields.Dialogue Text: I'll sell it.

fields.Title: Perception (Smell): "Are these the victim's clothes? The..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Are these the victim's clothes? The smell is not nearly as bad as the cadaver. These clothes could not have been in contact with the deceased for more than two days after his death.

fields.Title: You: "Reach for it."
fields.Dialogue Text: Reach for it.

fields.Title: You: ""Nope.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nope."

fields.Title: You: ""You think someone from the Whirlin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You think someone from the Whirling might have been... involved maybe?"

fields.Title: Interfacing: "Not just any man's. This dense curs..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Not just any man's. This dense cursive -- it's *yours*.

fields.Title: You: ""What is this?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What is this?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""What are you *talking* about?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What are you *talking* about?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Yes." He nods. "...if we're still..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes." He nods. "...if we're still assuming the clothes were taken off to get to the armour. They must have stripped him of it fast, the scavengers. In a matter of days."

fields.Title: Composure: "Easier said than done -- how could..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Easier said than done -- how could this pathetic cabbage of copy paper and plastic ever become *très disco*?"

fields.Title: You: "Alright then. Seems like a good ide..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Alright then. Seems like a good idea. Right after the garbage, of course. (Accept.)

fields.Title: You: ""Okay, I'll do that.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, I'll do that."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Oh." He pauses. "It *might* also b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh." He pauses. "It *might* also be evidence. The mob could have disposed of something in there. We should get it open."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Trash? Food waste from the cafeter..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Trash? Food waste from the cafeteria? They lock these containers to keep the derelicts from flocking in. Could be evidence too."

fields.Title: Interfacing: "You've done this before. The moveme..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You've done this before. The movements are recorded in your elbows, the methodology in your fingers... you're used to this.

fields.Title: You: ""Another time maybe." [Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: "Another time maybe." [Leave.]

fields.Title: Trash Container: "It's just organic waste, cold and s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's just organic waste, cold and slimy on your hands. Apple and potato peels mostly, unidentified sludge, and the occasional chicken bone thrown in for good measure. But hey...

fields.Title: You: "I am into hi-fi!"
fields.Dialogue Text: I am into hi-fi!

fields.Title: Trash Container: "All you see is a broken mug with a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: All you see is a broken mug with a racist depiction of *the yellow man* frolicking in saffron.

fields.Title: You: ""That's all, I think.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's all, I think."

fields.Title: Trash Container: "Something larger -- a clipboard! A..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Something larger -- a clipboard! A blue plastic clipboard with moist papers hanging from it. They look badly damaged, but you can still make out forms and notes. Written in a *man's* handwriting...

fields.Title: You: ""It must have been cramping my styl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It must have been cramping my style."

fields.Title: Empathy: "His eyes express a rare condolence...."
fields.Dialogue Text: His eyes express a rare condolence. Then he picks it up:

fields.Title: Trash Container: "You crawl out of the trash containe..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You crawl out of the trash container. The lid clangs shut. The fresh air rushes into your lungs, but does not clear them of the garbage stink.
fields.Sequence: PlayAnimation(Tequila Sunset, lid_close)->Message(lidClosed); PlayAnimation(bin_lid, lid_close); ShowActualHeld()@Message(lidClosed);

fields.Title: Drama: "It's remarkable how he can keep a s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's remarkable how he can keep a straight face. Take note -- the lieutenant is well versed in dead-panning. Many of the things he says could be meant in jest.

fields.Title: You: ""There is no Remote Viewers Divisio..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There is no Remote Viewers Division, is there?"

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "*Forget* about it? Like you forgot..."
fields.Dialogue Text: *Forget* about it? Like you forgot about your life? No! You cannot forget your own body, and your body cannot forget...

fields.Title: Half Light: "THE PRYBAR!"
fields.Dialogue Text: THE PRYBAR!

fields.Title: Trash Container: "The trash container has *somehow* b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The trash container has *somehow* been unlocked. It's all for you, Harry. The smell of rotten food rises up as you climb inside. This is where you belong...

fields.Title: Interfacing: "No, searching for evidence in the t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No, searching for evidence in the trash.

fields.Title: You: ""That's it, I can't pry it open.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's it, I can't pry it open."

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Don't! Maybe you shouldn't..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Don't! Maybe you shouldn't...

fields.Title: You: "Search the food waste."
fields.Dialogue Text: Search the food waste.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""We should return later, officer. I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We should return later, officer. I don't think we were thorough enough. There may be more in there."

fields.Title: Trash Container: "That's too bad, because none of tho..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That's too bad, because none of those things are actually in there. There's just food waste and crisp wrappings.

fields.Title: Trash Container: "Only in its social sensibility."
fields.Dialogue Text: Only in its social sensibility.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""This is a military type over-garme..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is a military type over-garment. No label or serial number -- this is the kind of rib-knit shirt that's worn over light armour to conceal it in an urban scenario..." He nods to himself. "Anything more?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Yes it is, look." He points to it...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes it is, look." He points to it. "This plastic has the RCM street grid on it. You've even got an autopsy form..." A miserable looking slip of paper sticks to the board.

fields.Title: You: "*Mine*? What is it doing in trash?"
fields.Dialogue Text: *Mine*? What is it doing in trash?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It would also not hurt to start ta..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It would also not hurt to start taking notes on the case." He peers into the trash, where soggy cartons and rags stink, uninvitingly. "Now, tell me what your eagle eyes see. Or are we finished?"

fields.Title: You: ""Night, Kim.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Night, Kim."

fields.Title: You: ""Wow! Could we get them here?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wow! Could we get them here?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Mhm." He leans in to inspect the l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Mhm." He leans in to inspect the lock.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Or we could ask for a key from the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Or we could ask for a key from the manager of the Whirling-in-Rags. He probably has one."

fields.Title: Interfacing: "Good practice for dumpster diving."
fields.Dialogue Text: Good practice for dumpster diving.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Just a feeling. A warning from some..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Just a feeling. A warning from some part of you.

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "No matter how strong you think you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No matter how strong you think you are, this is really not something you should be attempting to do with your bare hands.

fields.Title: You: "Force time -- jam the tool under th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Force time -- jam the tool under the lid and pull!
fields.tooltip1: Cuno said to aim for the staple.

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: (CheckItem("prybar")  or  CheckItem("kvalsund_multitool"))  and  Variable["yard.trash_container_open"] == false  and  Variable["TASK.open_trash_container"]

fields.Title: Cuno: ""We should find his gun and kill so..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We should find his gun and kill someone with it."

fields.Title: Trash Container: "You betcha."
fields.Dialogue Text: You betcha.

fields.Title: You: "Bag the trousers."
fields.Dialogue Text: Bag the trousers.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Information from that *source* has..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Information from that *source* has truly been invaluable to the investigation. I cannot wait to hear more."

fields.Title: You: "Open the lid again."
fields.Dialogue Text: Open the lid again.

fields.Title: You: ""It has a foreboding quality to it...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It has a foreboding quality to it. Maybe I *needed* to lose it, for the Great Bloodletting to begin?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Boring? Try *dangerous*. You shoul..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Boring? Try *dangerous*. You should do a thorough inventory of that -- be sure some has not fallen into the hands of the RCM's enemies: organized crime, or worse... Official notes sometimes contain informants' names, even undercover operatives."

fields.Title: You: "Say nothing."
fields.Dialogue Text: Say nothing.

fields.Title: You: "[Close the lid.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Close the lid.]

fields.Title: Tutorial Agent: "You've acquired an interactable ite..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You've acquired an interactable item. Investigate this item further by going to the INTERACT tab in your INVENTORY.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""We should still access this contai..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We should still access this container. There may be evidence in there."

fields.Title: You: ""What is the Remote Viewers Divisio..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What is the Remote Viewers Division?"

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Prybar, crowbar, leverage displacem..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Prybar, crowbar, leverage displacement tool of the gods. Your hands have held its paint-flaked metal one hundred thousand times.

fields.Title: You: "Time for bed. Crawl inside..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Time for bed. Crawl inside...
fields.Alternate1: Time for bed, Hobocop. Crawl inside...

fields.Title: Logic: "Now that your ledger is back in you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Now that your ledger is back in your possession, it feels like you should do something... *important*.

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "You force open the sealed metal lid..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You force open the sealed metal lid with your goddamn *bare hands*. It is open now. It could not resist your supra-human strength.

fields.Title: Trash Container: "You betcha. You know -- this awfull..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You betcha. You know -- this awfully *colonial* mug reminds you of another one, doesn't it? Anyway...

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Cuno's gotta say, man, that was un..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Cuno's gotta say, man, that was unimpressive. The fuck were you trying to do?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""You are. The prybar is quite satis..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You are. The prybar is quite satisfying and handy." He nods, without the slightest hint of irony. "But you are just not good enough at prying. We should get the keys."

fields.Title: You: ""I was trying to open the trash.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I was trying to open the trash."

fields.Title: You: "Look under the boxes of carton."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look under the boxes of carton.

fields.Title: You: "This makes a lot of sense."
fields.Dialogue Text: This makes a lot of sense.

fields.Title: You: ""I think I didn't want to be a cop..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I think I didn't want to be a cop anymore, so I threw it away."
fields.Alternate1: "I think I didn't want to be a cop anymore. That's why I tried to flush my cop life down the toilet."

fields.Title: You: ""Someone from the Whirling threw it..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Someone from the Whirling threw it in the trash? I don't know. I'm boring."

fields.Title: Cunoesse: ""No, Cuno, it's just *bino!*""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, Cuno, it's just *bino!*"

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "What are you talking about? No one'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What are you talking about? No one's out to get you -- get real man! Upgrade that cop-ledger!

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Looks like we found your paperwork.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Looks like we found your paperwork."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Tell me, does your bad ass see mor..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Tell me, does your bad ass see more in there or are we done here?" The lieutenant peers into the trash.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "He puts the cigarette back, and say..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He puts the cigarette back, and says: "Me too."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Good night, detective," he says, w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good night, detective," he says, with more gentleness than you've heard from him before.

fields.Title: Trash Container: "The container remains as inviting a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The container remains as inviting as a coffin. It is ready whenever you are.

fields.Title: Trash Container: "Well it is a *container*. Maybe you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Well it is a *container*. Maybe you're prioritizing it?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I agree. We should get someone fro..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I agree. We should get someone from the Remote Viewers Division here."

fields.Title: You: "Say nothing."
fields.Dialogue Text: Say nothing.

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Unreal.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Unreal."

fields.Title: Trash Container: "The container sounds a muffled gong..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The container sounds a muffled gong.
fields.Sequence: PlayAnimation(Tequila Sunset, lid_close)->Message(lidClosed); PlayAnimation(bin_lid, lid_close); ShowActualHeld()@Message(lidClosed);

fields.Title: You: "I don't know, it seems foreboding t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I don't know, it seems foreboding to me somehow. Like there's something in there that's out to get me.

fields.Title: Trash Container: "The smell of rotten food rises up a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The smell of rotten food rises up at you as you climb inside the trash container.

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "The morning will never come."
fields.Dialogue Text: The morning will never come.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""We could try using a prybar -- the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We could try using a prybar -- there's one in my motor carriage. Or..."

fields.Title: Jump to: [Trash Container: "The garbage stinks in front of you,..."]
Trash Container: "You pick out a broken mug, with an..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You pick out a broken mug, with an oddly racist depiction of *the yellow man* frolicking in saffron.

fields.Title: Interfacing: "Your fingers start to itch just loo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your fingers start to itch just looking at that padlock...

fields.Title: Trash Container: "Something slimy catches your eye..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Something slimy catches your eye...

fields.Title: Half Light: "*Full* of itself. Content, happy yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: *Full* of itself. Content, happy you failed. This snickering trash container is having a grand old time.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Mhm..." The lieutenant briefly gla..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Mhm..." The lieutenant briefly glances at the mug, then returns his sight to the trash.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""See?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "See?"

fields.Title: You: ""The handwriting -- it's mine.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "The handwriting -- it's mine."

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Challenge accepted. You should be o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Challenge accepted. You should be on the lookout for stylistic elements that elevate this cabbage to heights unforeseeable.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "He is as silent as the night."
fields.Dialogue Text: He is as silent as the night.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "Darkness engulfs you. The stink of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Darkness engulfs you. The stink of rot nearly knocks you out. For a minute you can smell cigarette smoke wafting in from outside.
fields.Sequence: PlayAnimation(Tequila Sunset, lid_sleep); PlayAnimation(bin_lid, lid_sleep); FocusCamera(Bin_Cam)@1; PlayAnimation(Kim Kitsuragi, StartSmoking)@5; PlayAnimation(Kim Cigarette, StartSmoking)@5; SemiBlack(true,2)@9;

fields.Title: Trash Container: "The lock says Whirling-in-Rags. May..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lock says Whirling-in-Rags. Maybe the proprietor has the key? Who knows what secrets wait inside...

fields.Title: You: "Forget about the prybar."
fields.Dialogue Text: Forget about the prybar.

fields.Title: You: "I should... start taking proper not..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I should... start taking proper notes on the case?

fields.Title: Trash Container: "There's a creaking sound as the pry..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There's a creaking sound as the prybar slips under the lid. You hang from it, like a moron, huffing and puffing. Clearly the technique is wrong -- but nothing else comes to mind.

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Yeah, I know but what were you try..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, I know but what were you trying to do pig?"

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "There is. But you won't *like* it...."
fields.Dialogue Text: There is. But you won't *like* it. Sweat forms on your brow, your hand is still on the lid...

fields.Title: Interfacing: "'Maybe you shouldn't...' Of course..."
fields.Dialogue Text: 'Maybe you shouldn't...' Of course you should! This is your time to shine, Hobocop! Dive into that dumpster for extra content!

fields.Title: Jump to: [Kim Kitsuragi: ""Alright. We should go to Garte aga..."]
You: ""Yeah, we need to ask the kids who..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, we need to ask the kids who put them here."

fields.Title: You: ""Okay." (Proceed.)"
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay." (Proceed.)

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""There's a *lot* of it too." He nod..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There's a *lot* of it too." He nods approvingly. "*And* you've got an autopsy form in there -- in the back. That light pink copy paper." A miserable looking slip of paper sticks to the board.

fields.Title: Cuno: ""You askin' me now? It's some shit,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You askin' me now? It's some shit, copper. How should I know?"

fields.Title: Trash Container: "Not much to see here anymore. Just..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Not much to see here anymore. Just a burnt apron and some kitchen towels.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "A few words also come through the m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A few words also come through the metal: "Good night, detective." But they dissipate around you like the smoke; you hear the lieutenant's footfall carry him away.

fields.Title: Tutorial Agent: "You've acquired an interactable ite..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You've acquired an interactable item. Investigate this item further by going to the INTERACT tab in your INVENTORY.

fields.Title: You: ""Lieutenant, what do you think coul..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Lieutenant, what do you think could be in there?"

fields.Title: Trash Container: "A box falls into pieces in your han..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A box falls into pieces in your hands: Batiste *Soleil* cereal. There are plastic pasta packages below, and *Turbo* noodles. Nothing of note, however.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "The rest of the rags are just kitch..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The rest of the rags are just kitchen-variety waste. Just garbage.

fields.Title: Tutorial Agent: "Some items, such as the ledger you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Some items, such as the ledger you found, are interactable. Go to your INVENTORY and select the INTERACT tab to read your paperwork.

fields.Title: Logic: "An interesting little clue. Let's s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: An interesting little clue. Let's see where this goes. Clues have a way of magically connecting to other clues -- down the road...

fields.Title: Trash Container: "And... what's this?"
fields.Dialogue Text: And... what's this?

fields.Title: Half Light: "WHAT IS THIS? Your triceps ache for..."
fields.Dialogue Text: WHAT IS THIS? Your triceps ache for the metal to bend, but it resists... this calls for a potent curse to help break it's resistance. Utter the POWER WORDS!

fields.Title: You: "Hang from the prybar with all your..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Hang from the prybar with all your weight.

fields.Title: Cunoesse: ""No he don't! He fuckin' lost it! T..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No he don't! He fuckin' lost it! The ape's lost the key too."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Let's ask the manager for the key,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Let's ask the manager for the key, this is clearly not working."

fields.Title: You: "Dig in Hobocop-style -- for extra c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Dig in Hobocop-style -- for extra content.

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["yard.trash_interfacing_deluxe_content"]  and  CheckItem("yellow_man_mug") == false  and  Variable["yard.trash_found_mug"] == false

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Cadaverine odour is faint." The li..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Cadaverine odour is faint." The lieutenant smells them. "If these belonged to the deceased, they were removed when he was still in the early stages of decay."
fields.Alternate1: "The victim's clothes?" The lieutenant smells them. "Cadaverine odour is faint. If these belonged to the deceased, they were removed when he was still in the early stages of decay."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""*Guitar* mark blue jeans. Pockets..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "*Guitar* mark blue jeans. Pockets empty." The lieutenant quickly searches the jeans. "Or *emptied*? He wore them with a belt, too, a wide belt -- the loops appear stretched, but..." He looks into the container.

fields.Title: Trash Container: "A drab long-sleeved shirt, olive-co..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A drab long-sleeved shirt, olive-coloured, appears from the food waste, dripping with pus.

fields.Title: You: ""A thrown out towel, a mug. That's..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "A thrown out towel, a mug. That's all."

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Nothing. It's nothing. Nothing more..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Nothing. It's nothing. Nothing more to see here.

fields.Title: You: "Elbows out, there's nothing more he..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Elbows out, there's nothing more here.

fields.Title: Authority: "Hey, maybe it's your paperwork, off..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Hey, maybe it's your paperwork, officer?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Officer, this is an official piece..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Officer, this is an official piece of paperwork. It probably contains notes on *numerous* ongoing investigations -- and could even list undercover operatives. Informants. I suggest integrating it into your *style*. For all our sakes."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Well..." He doesn't know what to s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Well..." He doesn't know what to say.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Did he? I must have drifted away....."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Did he? I must have drifted away... somewhere between the copious mentions of pigs and homo-sexuality."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Fuck yourself, binoclard!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Fuck yourself, binoclard!"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""There isn't.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "There isn't."

fields.Title: You: ""There is no need for sarcasm. I ju..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "There is no need for sarcasm. I just feel strongly about it, that's all. Maybe it's not connected to the case, but still."

fields.Title: You: ""It's extrasensory perception. What..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's extrasensory perception. Whatever is in there holds a special *significance*."

fields.Title: You: ""*Or*, lieutenant?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "*Or*, lieutenant?"

fields.Title: Trash Container: "You see: milk, an egg-rest with one..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You see: milk, an egg-rest with one broken egg in it, some pasta wrapper... Picking up the soggy packages somehow feels familiar.

fields.Title: You: "Open the padlock with the key."
fields.Dialogue Text: Open the padlock with the key.

fields.Title: You: ""The FUCK kind of metal is this, th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The FUCK kind of metal is this, this is fucking SHIT!"

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Quit pushin' the blame on the meta..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Quit pushin' the blame on the metal piggo. Metal's fine. It's your arm that's shit."

fields.Title: You: "Let it go."
fields.Dialogue Text: Let it go.

fields.Title: You: "Didn't I just have a premonition th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Didn't I just have a premonition that *there's something in there*?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""No-no. We need to investigate now...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No-no. We need to investigate now." Just like that, he opens the lid.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Not really. All we know is -- the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Not really. All we know is -- the victim's clothes are in the trash, the lid was locked, and this establishment had the key. It's just a *small* loose thread."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Tell me, *see-eth* your bad ass mo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Tell me, *see-eth* your bad ass more in there or are we done here?" The lieutenant peers into the trash.

fields.Title: You: ""I'd rather not to talk about it ri..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'd rather not to talk about it right now."

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: CheckItem("key_trash_container")  and  Variable["yard.trash_container_open"] == false  and  Variable["TASK.open_trash_container"]

fields.Title: Empathy: "Whatever he may feel in this moment..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Whatever he may feel in this moment is locked away deep inside him.

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "He's being sarcastic. Do *not* ask..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's being sarcastic. Do *not* ask what the Remote Viewers Division is.

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Really? Your muscles are down with..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Really? Your muscles are down with either one.

fields.Title: You: "It's not a *pry*bar, it's a crowbar..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's not a *pry*bar, it's a crowbar.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""We *might* want to ask for a key f..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We *might* want to ask for a key from the manager of the Whirling-in-Rags. He probably has one. And he also has *information*."
